parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the brake booster pump can cause the brake pedal to feel soft or spongy, leading to extended stopping distances, which can increase the risk of accidents.
symptoms: The brake pedal feels soft or spongy
the brake pedal has a delayed return to its normal position
the brake pedal has a sudden loss of pressure
the ABS
traction control
and brake warning lights are illuminated
the brakes make a hissing or pumping noise.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the headlights can cause reduced visibility, increasing the risk of accidents, especially at night or in low-light conditions.
symptoms: Headlights burn out frequently
often simultaneously
with no warning; low beam headlights fail more frequently than high beams; headlights may work intermittently or dimly; replacing bulbs does not solve the problem.
